        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "X-linked immunodeficiency with magnesium defect Epstein-Barr virus infection and neoplasia is a rare combined T and B cell immunodeficiency characterized by recurrent sinopulmonary and viral infections persistent elevated Epstein-Barr virus (EBV) viremia and increased susceptibility to EBV-associated B-cell lymphoproliferative disorders. Immunological analyses show normal lymphocyte count or mild to moderate lymphopenia inverted CD4:CD8 T-cell ratio and hypogammaglobulinemias."
        },
